headline: FFIV Q4 Deep Dive: AI Adoption, Hybrid Multi-Cloud, and Regulatory Tailwinds Drive Results
summary: Application security provider F5 (NASDAQ:FFIV) reported Q4 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 7.3% year on year to $822.5 million. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($780 million at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 4.7% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.45 per share was 21.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
